sentences: Manfredo Irmin Fest (May 13, 1936 – October 8, 1999) was a legally blind bossa nova and jazz pianist and keyboardist from Brazil.
He was born in Porto Alegre, Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, and he died at 63 years old in Tampa Bay, Florida.
His initial musical training had been classical, but at 17 years old, he became interested in the jazz works of George Shearing and Bill Evans.
In 1961, Fest graduated in piano from the University of Rio Grande do Sul.
One year later, he started his musical career playing in bars, clubs and pubs.
In 1963, he recorded his first LP, called Bossa nova, nova bossa.
In the 1970s he traveled to the United States where he worked with Sérgio Mendes.
His American debut album Manifestations was released in 1978.
Fest died of liver failure at the age of 63 in Tampa, Florida, not far from his home in Palm Harbor, where he had lived for 12 years.
